  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A randomized controlled trial to compare for the efficacy and tolerability of denosumab and
      oral alendronate in the management of glucocorticoid induced osteoporosis
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Study design: an open-label randomized controlled trial Duration of study: 12 months

      Treatment arms:

        1. Denosumab: a total of 2 doses in a period of 12 months

        2. Oral alendronate: weekly dose in a period of 12 months Target sample size: 220 patients
           (110 patients in each arm)
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
